 gave birth to a distinct form of radical politics that brought together the egalitarian culture of North Atlantic maritime communities with the revolutionary era's constitutional republicanism. The attempt to build a radical maritime republic failed, but the red flag that flew from the masts of mutinous ships survived to become the most enduring global symbol of class struggle, economic justice, and republican liberty to this day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aMutinyxPolitical aspectszNorth Atlantic Regiony18th century. 0aMutinyxPolitical aspectszNorth Atlantic Regiony19th century. 0aRadicalismy18th century. 0aRadicalismy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Maritime History & Piracy .2bisacsh  aage of revolution.  aatlantic history.  aatlantic revolution.  abritish navy.  acapitalism.  acaptains.  aclass struggle.  aconstitutional republicanism.  adutch navy.  aeconomic justice.  aempire.  afrench navy.  ainsurrectionary.  ainternationalism.  alate 18th century maritime history.  amaritime community.  amutiny.  anaval seamen.  anavy.  anobility.  anorth atlantic.  apiracy.  apirates.  aradical maritime republic.  aradical politics.  arepublican liberty.  ascandinavian navy.  ashipboard mutiny.  asiege.  atransnational.  aviolent conflict.  awar.  aworking class.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020